@jcommelin Yeah I'd appreciate review(s). I found that [setting `priority := low` for all but one IsTwoSided instance](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/17930/commits/a3ff84c95840c69b67a3ad1b60a296efd782b8b8) has a small speedup effect, and [restoring the shortcut instance `Ideal.instHasQuotient`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/17930/commits/bc0b9b26d71ecefcb655076e789398e20800384d) has a large speedup effect (from 0.44/0.55% to 0.28/0.34%). Adding another [shortcut instance in the commutative case](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/17930#issuecomment-2482715548) further reduced the numbers to 0.24/0.24%. Then I ran out of ideas to improve performance further.

I've investigated why AdjoinRoot got slower, and I've found e.g. [AdjoinRoot.quotMapOfEquivQuotMapCMapSpanMk_symm_mk](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/AdjoinRoot.html#AdjoinRoot.quotMapOfEquivQuotMapCMapSpanMk_symm_mk) now requires 7585 heartbeats (compared to 3512 originally) and [PowerBasis.quotientEquivQuotientMinpolyMap_apply_mk](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/AdjoinRoot.html#PowerBasis.quotientEquivQuotientMinpolyMap_apply_mk) now requires 19028 (compared to 6146 originally). I found that replacing some occurrences of  `Ideal.Quotient.mk` by a CommRing-specific version `mk'` that doesn't take [IsTwoSided] as an argument could reduce the heartbeats a lot but could sometimes also increase the heartbeats (see table below), and for the slowest decls it's not very effective (e.g. reduces 19028 to 15297), so I doubt that's the way to go.
